Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @curry powder{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4 servings); cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds} (you'll use more curry powder later).

Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4), and @salt{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Zest and quarter @lemon{1} (for 4 servings, zest one lemon and quarter both). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}.

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine juice from half the lemon, @water{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings), and @sugar{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4). Stir in @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Microwave for ~{1%minute}. Add juice from remaining lemon and @salt{big pinch}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, @low-fat yogurt{2%tbsp}, @curry powder{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4), and a pinch of lemon zest to taste (you'll use the rest of the curry powder in the next step). Season with @salt{}. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and remaining curry powder.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. TIP: If chicken begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

During the last minute of cooking, reduce heat to medium and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted. Spoon butter over chicken.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @golden raisins{1%oz}, @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), @salt{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4), and remaining lemon zest to taste.

Drain cabbage; stir in half the cilantro. Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide rice between bowls; top with chicken and cabbage. Drizzle chicken with sauce and garnish with remaining cilantro. Serve.

> Sometimes you just need a little curry to spice up your week—and for those times, our chefs have your back. Tonight, they spiced up not one, not two, but THREE components of this meal with curry spices: curried chicken, curry rice with golden raisins, and lemon curry sauce. Together with pickled red cabbage, these curried chicken bowls pack flavor into every bite.